    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in a bowl<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>spiced tomato paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spiced tomato paste</strong> to the pan with 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [225ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for an initial 7-10 min or until the sauce has reduced slightly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>fish fillet[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>over the <strong>chopped fish </strong>and gently rub the spices all over the fish</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onions</strong> finely</p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce,</strong> pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has reduced, add the <strong>chopped fish </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>chipotle spiced fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fish is cooking, combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with a squeeze of <strong>lime</strong> <strong>juice </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>in a bowl<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>lime mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> tortillas</strong> to a plate and pop them in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 20 secs on high or until warmed through</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-cod-wholemeal-tacos-with-lime-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion, chipotle spiced fish</strong>, <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>lime mayo</strong> evenly between the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>tortillas</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
